  "text": "The mechanisms underpinning the changes observed in our SHG cohort are unknown, but possibly similar to those affecting Dutch Famine survivors exposed to undernutrition in early gestation. Interestingly, periconceptional exposure to the Dutch Famine was associated with hypomethylation of the igf2 gene in later adult life [CITATION_1] . Thus, the study of Heijmans et al [CITATION_2] raises the possibility that epigenetic modification of gene expression may be a possible mechanism programming metabolism in our SHG cohort.",
